{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1562c7d6-0da9-4d7d-b788-58c72e3614b6","content":"Use `dotnet watch test` — it monitors your files and re-runs tests automatically on every save:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test --filter \"RemoveStock_ExceedsAvailable_ThrowsException\"\n```\n\nThe `--filter` flag scopes it to just your failing test for fast feedback. Once it's running, every time you save `InventoryServiceTests.cs`, the test re-runs automatically.\n\n**As for the bug itself** — `RemoveStock` never validates the quantity. It subtracts even when stock is insufficient, instead of throwing. Fix line 37:\n\n```csharp\npublic void RemoveStock(string sku, int quantity)\n{\n    var current = _stock.GetValueOrDefault(sku);\n    if (quantity > current)\n        throw new InvalidOperationException($\"Cannot remove {quantity} from {sku}, only {current} available.\");\n    _stock[sku] = current - quantity;\n}\n```\n\nWant me to apply the fix and start the watch runner?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"177fb942-79a3-46db-932d-c52f3c1259dd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to set up hot reload for their test project. With .NET and MSTest using Microsoft.Testing.Platform, they can use `dotnet test --hotreload` or `dotnet watch test`. Let me check what's available.\n\nThe project uses:\n- .NET 10.0\n- MSTest 3.8.0\n- Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner\n\nFor hot reload with tests, the best approach is `dotnet watch test` which will re-run tests whenever files change. Let me show them how to set this up.\n\nActually, with the Microsoft.Testing.Platform runner, there might also be `dotnet test --hotreload` support. \n\nI think `dotnet watch test` is the most straightforward option to recommend here.","outputTokens":416,"requestId":"7684:2F6FBA:C5B8A2:E486DA:69F2B1D7"},"id":"31c4671a-ee4a-4030-a082-804c5313f950","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:35:29.047Z","parentId":"5e9c9f5f-2757-4318-8ad3-8d7821fb8adb"}
